Title: The only computer science book worth reading twice?
Description:
I was talking to one of my students earlier, and lent him a book to
read over summer. It was only after he’d left that I realised that —
for me at any rate — the book I’d given him is probably the most
seminal work in the whole of computer science, and certainly the book
that’s most influenced my career and research interests.

Title: TS018: Vesioning
Description:
In this session, we will discuss versioning according to The Standard. We will touch on three main areas in versioning which are:
What to version?
When to version?
How to version?

Check out The Standard here for more information:
https://github.com/hassanhabib/The-Standard
